Before I was a world champ.. I was little Sammy.. I’ll always be little Sammy. From Koloa bridge and hitchhiking to school and the beach everyday to traveling the world making my dreams come true! Anything is possible if you put in the time and dedication❤️… I’ll never forget where I came from and who helped me get there💪… @brandon_buza spent almost a decade stacking these clips in this segment for our movie THE GARDEN! KUG BODYBOARDING.. I remember seeing a hat one day at his house that had KUG on it and something just called out to me to ask what KUG stood for! KAUA’I UNDERGROUND.. it just meant so much to me after I got told the origins and meaning of it and I’ve forever lived by it.. the guys who paved the way for me I’ll forever be grateful! @clsonoda @budztriad @brandon_buza @jonahdias808 @drag_em_hard @kolomona1_ @unkopaul @chilosan @kh6969 @birdmonmatheny love you guys thanks for believing in me thru it all❤️ I’ll never stop believing in the next generation because the guys I looked up to never gave up on me! KUG FOR LIFE 💥

“It is what it is and that’s just how it goes”  Story time below if you wanna learn about me 🤠

That’s it for me in the Prone division of the @maldivespromv Went down in round 5 today in prone🫡 Still got the DK division round three Tomorrow! #skitzo

Never easy losing this far away from home, or losing at all this early in any event. Especially when you fall short of personal goals. But you gotta trust in the process! Even when it’s difficult. Comps are comps! but life is life!

Sometimes you get mad,sometimes your content and just brush it off, but after every heat loss is time to reflect and identify mistakes that were made. but today I took it a little deeper spiritually and mentally in a good learning who I really am type of way (after I got mad of course duh😂) I just thought to myself like what I really wanna do in life. 

I know I want to keep competing for many years to come, but I really thought to myself for the first time in years like what I wanna do with my life I’ll be 30 in three years.

I deeply thought about having a family today after I lost. Like talking in my head telling myself like you know this ain’t gonna support a family when you have one right? Especially when you’re losing!When am I gonna stop living in this fantasy world where bodyboarding is my career and I’m a professional bodyboarder? 

I don’t have a board sponsor and I don’t get paid? 

Then I thought to myself “kid look where you are right now, you’re in the Maldives you always wanted to come here before you even knew about the tour”  you’re living the life you wanted to when you were a little kid at the beach dreaming of places like this! 

I just wanna thank bodyboarding for bringing me a roller coaster of emotions over the years,countless friendships that will last forever, memories I’ll never forget and the highest highs I’ve ever felt! Learning to sit back and enjoy the ride and take it all in!

trusting in the process this year 100% and I feel that I’m heading down my correct path in life finally with the right mindset 🖤 mahalo ke akua ! 

Mahalo Piha to anyone that has supported my “career” over the years! 

🎥 @liquefy_maldives @ibcworld_tour @eric_within

social_posts.post_text:
Never give up is the message . @sammymorretino had the goal of qualifying into the top 16 this season, and he knew he would make it no matter what.

#ibcworldtour #ibcworldtour2023 #bodyboard #bodyboarding #sal #southamericanleg

Life’s a lot like this big airdrop, sometimes you stick it and sometimes you get worked! 

I’ve been getting pretty worked lately😅
 
Recently I’ve learned Just when you think it’s a bad as it gets it gets even worse. 

People that you thought would always be there for you aren’t there at all. 

I constantly ask myself if it wasn’t for my bodyboarding accomplishments would anyone even care? 

 Would people still go out of their way to assist me? To comfort me? at the end of the day my bodyboarding accomplishments are just memories. 

I’m a still a human being, I still have feelings and I still struggle like everyone else on this planet. 

I look back and ask myself what I did to achieve all my accomplishments in life? It makes me proud knowing I persevered through my toughest times in life because of a little piece of foam! 

 Then I ask myself, what I’ve done to deserve the horrible things I’ve gone through in my life? 

Probably a lot of things. Wether my decisions were good or bad. They were my decisions and I chose to make them in the end. 

Probably a lot of karma coming back for my poor decisions I made growing up after my mom passed away.

So if I’ve ever wronged you in any way, was disrespectful towards you or mean to you, I would like to apologize for my actions towards you. 

Mahalo for letting me speak my mind on this! I’ve been holding this in for a long time and it feels good to let it out! 

Sincerely, Sammy Morretino
